import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='cx', bins=20)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude values across all London boroughs?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    chart = sns.barplot(x='name', y='cx', data=data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    max_longitude_borough = data.loc[data['cx'].idxmax()]['name']
    max_longitude_value = data['cx'].max()
    plt.axhline(y=max_longitude_value, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Max Longitude: {max_longitude_value:.2f} ({max_longitude_borough})')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('Which London borough has the highest longitude value?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    chart = sns.barplot(x='name', y='cy', data=data)
    plt.title('Which London borough has the highest latitude value?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    max_latitude = data['cy'].max()
    max_borough = data.loc[data['cy'] == max_latitude, 'name'].iloc[0]
    chart.axhline(max_latitude, ls='--', color='red', label=f'Max Latitude: {max_latitude:.2f} ({max_borough})')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
